This proof relies entirely on the given axioms and does not require any additional assumptions or lemmas. The steps are straightforward once we recognize that `K.call` can be used to simplify `(K ◁ x) ◁ I` directly to `x`. The use of `I` is somewhat arbitrary; any other bird would work equally well since `K.call` applies universally to all birds `x` and `y`. 

However, Lean requires us to specify a particular bird to apply, and `I` is as good a choice as any. 

